title: Kenosha Beef International Recalls Beef Product Due to Possible Listeria Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, Feb. 19, 2015 Kenosha Beef International, a Columbus, Ohio, establishment, is recalling approximately 21,427 pounds of ready-to-eat beefsteak patty product that may be contaminated with Listeria monocytogenes, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.The fully cooked beefsteak patties...
